"{\"uid\": \"inews.co.uk-sport-olympics-what-like-paris-eurostar-olympic-chaos-3191534\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"IMPARTIAL NEWS + INTELLIGENT DEBATE  Account  One in four trains into Paris is cancelled on the opening day of the Olympics after a co-ordinated attack on the French rail system  When the wiry representative from GB taekwondo hastily left his seat and purposely walked down the carriage, it was a sign that patience on board the Eurostar had worn very thin.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 357, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 70, \"end\": 75, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999968168, \"rank\": 3.188922454073921e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 159, \"end\": 165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9996382621686667, \"rank\": 0.0002317863144332635, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 213, \"end\": 215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9998137493914844, \"rank\": 0.00018565442952547576, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 329, \"end\": 337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"score\": 0.9999972701706127, \"rank\": 2.7298368724806696e-06, \"text\": \"Eurostar\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His is a sport in which self-control was a key tenet.\", \"from\": 358, \"to\": 411, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And who knows what sort of damage he could have done to a hapless conductor.\", \"from\": 412, \"to\": 488, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We were stopped at Lille for no apparent reason, having left late from King's Cross due to a series ofsabotages on the French high-speed railway network.\", \"from\": 490, \"to\": 643, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 509, \"end\": 514, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"score\": 0.9790418541153254, \"rank\": 0.021382481767432432, \"text\": \"Lille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\"}, {\"begin\": 561, \"end\": 565, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/King\", \"score\": 0.8226483375372744, \"rank\": 0.16570648652494135, \"text\": \"King\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/King\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/King\"}, {\"begin\": 609, \"end\": 615, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9996382621686667, \"rank\": 0.0002317863144332635, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The train was full - a smattering ofTeam GBrepresentatives (nobody instantly recognisable - they were all safely ensconced in their holding camps), tourists and media.\", \"from\": 644, \"to\": 811, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And after the seventh utterance of \\\"we are very sorry for your inconvenience\\\" in two languages, the feeling of bonhomie and joie de vivre had drained from the train.\", \"from\": 813, \"to\": 978, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 937, \"end\": 950, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joie_de_vivre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"joie de vivre\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joie_de_vivre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joie_de_vivre\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When the girl of around six shouted in a North American accent \\\"I am BORED of this\\\", the rest of the carriage empathised.\", \"from\": 980, \"to\": 1101, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1027, \"end\": 1035, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999769878483064, \"rank\": 1.8686329157653e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We were going to be at least an hour late arriving into Paris.\", \"from\": 1102, \"to\": 1164, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1158, \"end\": 1163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999968168, \"rank\": 3.188922454073921e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At Lille, the conductor informed us that we would be moving \\\"shortly\\\".\", \"from\": 1166, \"to\": 1236, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1169, \"end\": 1174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"score\": 0.9790418541153254, \"rank\": 0.021382481767432432, \"text\": \"Lille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Relative to what remained a mystery.\", \"from\": 1237, \"to\": 1273, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But at least there was a prospect of moving.\", \"from\": 1274, \"to\": 1318, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One in four trains were cancelled on Friday, which was not a good look for France on the day it is trying to show itself off to the world as open and peaceful.\", \"from\": 1320, \"to\": 1479, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1395, \"end\": 1401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9029449397058731, \"rank\": 0.10704894591520633, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It wasn't Eurostar's fault, of course.\", \"from\": 1481, \"to\": 1519, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1491, \"end\": 1499, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"score\": 0.9999972701706127, \"rank\": 2.7298368724806696e-06, \"text\": \"Eurostar\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This was apparently a co-ordinated attack on signal boxes, designed for maximum impact, but with minimal damage to human life.\", \"from\": 1520, \"to\": 1646, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Indeed, we could all be thankful that nobody was hurt or killed.\", \"from\": 1648, \"to\": 1712, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The vibe was more \\\"annoyed by industrial action\\\" than \\\"we are in the middle of an international incident\\\".\", \"from\": 1713, \"to\": 1819, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And the train staff were calm, friendly and as informative as they could be.\", \"from\": 1821, \"to\": 1897, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They gained bonus points for handing out little chocolates emblazoned with logos of variousOlympicgoverning bodies.\", \"from\": 1898, \"to\": 2013, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mine was team Netherlands.\", \"from\": 2014, \"to\": 2040, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2028, \"end\": 2039, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9999456640699956, \"rank\": 4.9896952760461656e-05, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the train groaned out of Lille and finally began to pick up speed, the GB taekwondo guy came back.\", \"from\": 2042, \"to\": 2143, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2070, \"end\": 2075, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"score\": 0.9790418541153254, \"rank\": 0.021382481767432432, \"text\": \"Lille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\"}, {\"begin\": 2116, \"end\": 2118, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9998137493914844, \"rank\": 0.00018565442952547576, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Turns out he had only gone out to get a cup of coffee.\", \"from\": 2144, \"to\": 2198, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See?\", \"from\": 2199, \"to\": 2203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Self-control.\", \"from\": 2204, \"to\": 2217, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His behaviour was an example to all of us.\", \"from\": 2218, \"to\": 2260, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Impartial news + intelligent debate  All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 2262, \"to\": 2319, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 2026 Associated Newspapers Limited.\", \"from\": 2320, \"to\": 2357, \"entities\": []}]}"